I"¯<h3 id="hot-rod-clients">Hot Rod Clients</h3>

<p>Hot Rod is a wire protocol that Infinispan clients use to talk to a remote grid. It is a binary, platform-independent protocol that was developed in the open as a part of Infinispan.</p>

<p>The Hot Rod <a href="https://infinispan.org/docs/stable/titles/hotrod_protocol/hotrod_protocol.html">specification</a> is available on-line, and several clients exist for this protocol.</p>
